page.title: 08Foxes,Deer and Rabbits
page.content: The foxes survive in the area because of the smaller rodents(for example,mice,rats and squirrels),rabbits and young or injured deer.All these are prey to the foxes.The foxes' dens are left alone and are away from the test areas used by the Ministry of Defence. The deer,especially the roe deer,also are seen in this area.They watch the men working at the Ministry of Defence but as soon as the deer realise that they are being watched,they run away. The rabbits have dominated much of the area even though they are the prey of the foxes.As with the deer,they only eat grasses and vegetation.
